# Dark pages (`page-dark`)

Some project pages use a **black page background**. Mark them with:

```html
<body class="page-dark">
```

## Behavior

- `html` + `body` background: **#000000** (including ultrawide side gutters)
- Default text on the page shell: **white** (`--color-text-on-dark`)
- Nav links, intro copy, and site footer invert to light-on-dark
- Theme sections inside the page keep their own section styles

## When to use

Apply `page-dark` only to full pages designed on black (e.g. `stream-packages.html`). Do not add to light pages like `hello-fresh.html` unless explicitly requested.

When the user says **"página con fondo negro"** or **"dark page"**, use `class="page-dark"` on `<body>`.
